---
import "../styles/global.css";
import Layout from "./layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <p>
    <span class="accent">misery.systems</span> is what I (affectionately) call my homelab.
  </p>

  <p>
    It's a small virtualized Kubernetes cluster. Specifically Talos running on three Proxmox nodes. I use it for learning, testing, and hosting a few personal projects.
  </p>

  <p>
    I wanted a name that was short and kind of funny, and I was out of better ideas. There's a long-running joke that Kubernetes can be a source of misery for its users.
  </p>

  <p>
    The individual nodes (as seen on the <a href="/about">about</a> page) came from asking ChatGPT for "misery-themed homelab hostnames" and picking the first three that were short, single words.
  </p>

  <p>If you've spent time with Kubernetes, that might be relatable.</p>
</Layout>
